# Core standards

## Code quality
- Prefer clean, production-ready code with proper error handling and structured logging.
- Avoid magic values; use constants/enums/config as appropriate.
- Make failure modes explicit (timeouts, retries where appropriate, meaningful error messages).

## UI quality (frontend work)
- Dark-mode first, fully responsive UI.
- Always include loading/empty/error states for async flows.
- Use toast notifications for user-visible success/failure events when appropriate.

## LLM usage (project-wide expectation)
- Use Instructor + LiteLLM for LLM calls with structured **Pydantic v2** outputs (avoid free-form parsing).
